### ============================================
### OrioSearch API - REST Client Tests
### ============================================
### Requires VS Code extension: REST Client (humao.rest-client)
### Start the stack first: docker compose up --build

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@apiKey = your-secret-key-here


### ============================================
### Health & Info
### ============================================

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###

### OpenAPI JSON spec
GET {{baseUrl}}/openapi.json

###

### LLM Tool Schema (OpenAI function-calling format)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tool-schema

###


### ============================================
### SEARCH - Basic
### ============================================

### Basic search (fast, snippets only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "python fastapi tutorial",
  "max_results": 5
}

###

### Search with topic = news
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "artificial intelligence",
  "topic": "news",
  "max_results": 5
}

###

### Search with time range filter
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "latest python release",
  "time_range": "week",
  "max_results": 3
}

###

### Minimal search (just query, all defaults)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "what is docker"
}

###


### ============================================
### SEARCH - Advanced (with content extraction)
### ============================================

### Advanced search - fetches and extracts full page content
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "how to use docker compose",
  "search_depth": "advanced",
  "max_results": 3
}

###

### Search with include_raw_content (basic depth + extracted content)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "redis caching best practices",
  "include_raw_content": true,
  "max_results": 2
}

###


### ============================================
### SEARCH - Images
### ============================================

### Search with images
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "cute cats",
  "include_images": true,
  "max_results": 5
}

###

### Advanced search with images and extraction
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "machine learning architecture diagrams",
  "search_depth": "advanced",
  "include_images": true,
  "max_results": 3
}

###


### ============================================
### SEARCH - Domain Filters
### ============================================

### Include only specific domains
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "python async",
  "include_domains": ["docs.python.org", "realpython.com"],
  "max_results": 5
}

###

### Exclude specific domains
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "javascript frameworks 2026",
  "exclude_domains": ["medium.com", "w3schools.com"],
  "max_results": 5
}

###


### ============================================
### SEARCH - Full featured (all params)
### ============================================

### Everything combined
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "self hosted search engine",
  "search_depth": "advanced",
  "topic": "general",
  "max_results": 5,
  "include_raw_content": true,
  "include_images": true,
  "exclude_domains": ["pinterest.com"],
  "time_range": "month"
}

###


### ============================================
### SEARCH - SSE Streaming
### ============================================
### Note: REST Client shows raw SSE text.
### Events: result, image, extraction, done, error

### Stream basic search results
POST {{baseUrl}}/search/stream
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: text/event-stream

{
  "query": "python async programming",
  "max_results": 3
}

###

### Stream with images
POST {{baseUrl}}/search/stream
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: text/event-stream

{
  "query": "cute cats",
  "include_images": true,
  "max_results": 3
}

###

### Stream advanced search with extraction
POST {{baseUrl}}/search/stream
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: text/event-stream

{
  "query": "fastapi best practices",
  "search_depth": "advanced",
  "max_results": 2
}

###


### ============================================
### EXTRACT - Content extraction
### ============================================

### Extract single URL (markdown format, default)
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": ["https://httpbin.org/html"]
}

###

### Extract multiple URLs (tests Redis pipeline batching)
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": [
    "https://httpbin.org/html",
    "https://httpbin.org/html",
    "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com"
  ],
  "format": "markdown"
}

###

### Extract with text format
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": ["https://httpbin.org/html"],
  "format": "text"
}

###

### Extract - mixed success and failure
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": [
    "https://httpbin.org/html",
    "https://thisdomaindoesnotexist99999.com/page"
  ]
}

###


### ============================================
### AUTH - API Key Authentication
### ============================================
### Enable auth in config.yaml first:
###   auth:
###     enabled: true
###     api_keys: ["your-secret-key-here"]

### Search with valid API key (200 when auth enabled)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "query": "test auth",
  "max_results": 1
}

###

### Search without API key (401 when auth enabled)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "test no auth",
  "max_results": 1
}

###

### Search with invalid API key (403 when auth enabled)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer invalid-key-here

{
  "query": "test bad auth",
  "max_results": 1
}

###

### Extract with API key
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "urls": ["https://httpbin.org/html"]
}

###

### Stream with API key
POST {{baseUrl}}/search/stream
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Accept: text/event-stream

{
  "query": "auth stream test",
  "max_results": 1
}

###


### ============================================
### Validation - Expected 422 errors
### ============================================

### Missing query field
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "max_results": 5
}

###

### max_results out of range (max 20)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "test",
  "max_results": 50
}

###

### Invalid search_depth enum
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "test",
  "search_depth": "ultra"
}

###

### Invalid topic enum
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "test",
  "topic": "finance"
}

###

### Invalid time_range enum
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "test",
  "time_range": "century"
}

###

### Empty body
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### Extract with no URLs (min 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": []
}

###

### Extract with too many URLs (max 20)
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": [
    "https://httpbin.org/html/1", "https://httpbin.org/html/2", "https://httpbin.org/html/3",
    "https://httpbin.org/html/4", "https://httpbin.org/html/5", "https://httpbin.org/html/6",
    "https://httpbin.org/html/7", "https://httpbin.org/html/8", "https://httpbin.org/html/9",
    "https://httpbin.org/html/10", "https://httpbin.org/html/11", "https://httpbin.org/html/12",
    "https://httpbin.org/html/13", "https://httpbin.org/html/14", "https://httpbin.org/html/15",
    "https://httpbin.org/html/16", "https://httpbin.org/html/17", "https://httpbin.org/html/18",
    "https://httpbin.org/html/19", "https://httpbin.org/html/20", "https://httpbin.org/html/21"
  ]
}

###

### Extract with invalid format
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": ["https://httpbin.org/html"],
  "format": "html"
}

###


### ============================================
### Request ID tracing
### ============================================

### Auto-generated X-Request-ID (check response headers)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###

### Custom X-Request-ID passed through
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: my-custom-trace-id-123

{
  "query": "trace id test",
  "max_results": 1
}

###
